"a.性急的，暴躁的 【英】 adj. 性急的，暴躁的(inso lent; peevish) 【记】 来自pet(不高兴)+ula nt→非常不高兴→暴 躁的 【同】 n.petulance 【例】 She becomes petulant when people disagree with her. adj. 性急易怒的 = insolent = peevish 【记】pet(v 拥抱; 发脾气), ulant－易怒的pet宠物, ul, ant蚂蚁: 你家的宠物见到蚂蚁就会打斗－易怒的读: petu烂踢－宠物烂踢－易怒的 【参】petulance读: pet烂撕－(n 易怒) 【记】pet + 音：吐，宠物吐，给宠物吃好吃的，它吐出来不吃发脾气；近于pettish 及peevish 易怒的,暴躁的 petulant (adj.)  1590s, ""immodest, wanton, saucy,"" from Middle French petulant (mid-14c.), from Latin petulantem (nominative petulans) ""wanton, froward, saucy, insolent,"" present participle of petere ""to attack, assail; strive after; ask for, beg, beseech"" (see petition (n.)). Meaning ""peevish, irritable"" first recorded 1775, probably by influence of pet (n.2). Related: Petulantly."
